<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, shrink-to-fit=no">
    <title>Register</title>

    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://stackpath.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/4.4.1/css/bootstrap.min.css"
        integrity="sha384-Vkoo8x4CGsO3+Hhxv8T/Q5PaXtkKtu6ug5TOeNV6gBiFeWPGFN9MuhOf23Q9Ifjh" crossorigin="anonymous">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/login.css">
</head>

<body class="text-center">
    <h1 class="h3 mb-3 font-weight-normal">Register</h1>
    <% if (messages.error) { %>
    <%= messages.error %>
    <% } %>
    
<form class="form-signin" action="/register" method=POST>
    <div>
        <label for="name" class="sr-only">Name</label>
        <input type="text" id="name" name="name" class="form-control" placeholder="Name" required autofocus>
    </div>
    <div>
        <label for="email" class="sr-only">Email</label>
        <input type="email" id="email" name="email" class="form-control" placeholder="Email address" required >
    </div>
    <div>
        <label for="password" class="sr-only">Password</label>
        <input type="password" id="password" name="password" class="form-control" placeholder="Password" required>
    </div>
    <button type="submit">Register</button>
</form>


<div class="form-signin">
    <h3>Test Controls</h3>
    <p>The home and login buttons are here to verify that access to the
        <b>/</b><i>{root}</i> and <b>/login</b> endpoints both redirect to /login if a user is not logged in;
        although this page should not appear is a user is logged in. This text and these buttons can be deleted in the final version of the site.</p>
    <a href="/" class="btn btn-info">Home</a>
    <a href="/login" class="btn btn-info">Login</a>
</div>